Definition.WordDefinition: Smoor \Smoor\, v. t. [AS. smorian; akin to D. & LG. smoren, G. schmoren to stew. Cf. {Smother}.] To suffocate or smother. [Written also {smore}.] [Obs. or Prov. Eng. & Scot.] --Sir T. More. Burns. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Smore \Smore\, v. t. To smother. See {Smoor}. [Obs.] [1913 Webster]
Some dying vomit blood, and some were smored. --Du Bartas. [1913 Webster]
